<h1 class="hero-h">What Is Claude Team? <em style="color:#00C853;font-style:italic;">Claude for B2B teams of 5-150.</em></h1>
<p class="hero-sub">Claude Team is the right tier for most $5M-$50M B2B companies adopting Claude. Here's exactly what's in it, what it costs, and how it differs from Pro and Enterprise.</p>
<div class="tldr"><div class="tldr-l">Short answer</div><p class="tldr-p">Claude Team is Anthropic's mid-tier business plan — \$30/user/month — designed for teams of ~5-150. Includes shared Projects, admin controls, no training on inputs, and centralized billing. The right starting point for most B2B mid-market AI rollouts.</p></div>
</div></div>

<section><div class="sec-inner"><h2 class="h2">What's included in Claude Team</h2><ul class="ul"><li><strong>Claude Sonnet</strong> as default model; Opus available per conversation.</li><li><strong>Claude Projects</strong> — shared, with team-wide knowledge and instructions.</li><li><strong>Admin console</strong> — user management, usage analytics, billing.</li><li><strong>No training on inputs</strong> — your conversations and Projects are not used to train Anthropic models.</li><li><strong>Centralized billing</strong> — single invoice for the whole team.</li><li><strong>Higher usage limits</strong> than Pro tier.</li></ul></div></section>
<section><div class="sec-inner"><h2 class="h2">How Team compares to other Claude tiers</h2></div></section>
<section><div class="sec-inner"><h2 class="h2">Why Team is the right starting point for most B2B mid-market</h2><ul class="ul"><li>Cost-effective at \$30/seat for the capability you get.</li><li>Has the business-critical features (no-training, admin controls).</li><li>No long sales process — sign up and provision today.</li><li>Easy to upgrade to Enterprise if you outgrow it.</li></ul></div></section>
<section><div class="sec-inner"><h2 class="h2">When to step up to Enterprise</h2><ul class="ul"><li>You need SSO (especially Okta, Azure AD) integration.</li><li>You need SCIM provisioning.</li><li>You need audit logging beyond what Team offers.</li><li>You handle PHI and need a Business Associate Agreement.</li><li>You need custom data retention policies.</li><li>You have 150+ seats.</li></ul></div></section>

<section><div class="sec-inner"><h2 class="h2">FAQ</h2>
<div class="faq-q"><h3 class="faq-qh">Does Claude Team train on my data?</h3><p class="faq-qa">No. Inputs to Claude Team are not used to train Anthropic models.</p></div>
<div class="faq-q"><h3 class="faq-qh">How quickly can I provision Claude Team?</h3><p class="faq-qa">Same day. Sign up via Anthropic, invite team members, start using.</p></div>
<div class="faq-q"><h3 class="faq-qh">Can I get a BAA on Claude Team?</h3><p class="faq-qa">BAAs are typically on Enterprise. If you handle PHI, upgrade to Enterprise.</p></div>
<div class="faq-q"><h3 class="faq-qh">What's the minimum number of seats?</h3><p class="faq-qa">5 seats. Below that, individual Pro accounts make more sense.</p></div>
<div class="faq-q"><h3 class="faq-qh">Can I expand to Enterprise later?</h3><p class="faq-qa">Yes, smoothly. Anthropic supports the upgrade path.</p></div>
</div></section>

